<body>

<div class="container">
  <div class="header">
    <h1>🐝 Stella Repository Index</h1>
    <p>Mills Act Tax Calculator for Palm Springs real estate valuation analysis</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Repository Overview -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>📋 Overview</h2>
    <p style="color: #9CA3AF; line-height: 1.6;">
      Stella is an interactive web-based tax calculator designed for analyzing the financial impact of California's Mills Act property tax restriction program. The calculator combines income capitalization valuation methods with short-term rental (STR) financial analysis to determine tax savings and rental viability.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Files Section -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>📁 Repository Files</h2>
    <div class="file-list">
      <div class="file-item">
        <div class="file-name">mills-act-calculator (2).html</div>
        <div class="file-desc">Single-page application. Contains HTML structure, embedded CSS (dark theme with gold/green/blue accents), and JavaScript calculator logic. 572 lines.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Application Architecture -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>⚙️ Architecture</h2>
    <div class="code-section">
      <div class="code-title">Application Structure</div>
      <p style="color: #9CA3AF; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6;">
        <strong>Single-File SPA (Single Page Application)</strong><br>
        • HTML: Header, content container, 5 tab sections<br>
        • CSS: Embedded (99 lines). Dark theme (#0B0F19 bg, #E5E7EB text)<br>
        • JavaScript: Embedded (449 lines). Pure vanilla JS, no frameworks<br>
        • Chart Library: Chart.js v4.4.1 (CDN)
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Core Data Model -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>💾 Core State Object (S)</h2>
    <div class="code-section">
      <div class="code-title">Primary Input Variables</div>
      <p style="color: #9CA3AF; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6;">
        <strong>Property &amp; Taxation:</strong> purchasePrice, marketValue, propTaxRate<br>
        <strong>Mills Act Valuation:</strong> monthlyFairRent, vacancyRate, monthlyOpEx, occupancyType<br>
        <strong>Cap Rate Components:</strong> interestComp, propTaxComp, remainingLife, improvementRatio<br>
        <strong>STR Metrics:</strong> nightlyRate, strOccupancy, totRate<br>
        <strong>Operating Costs:</strong> monthlyMortgage, monthlyInsurance, monthlyUtilities, monthlyLawn, monthlyPool, monthlyMaintenance<br>
        <strong>Tax Rates:</strong> fedRate, stateRate
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Calculation Engine -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>🧮 Calculation Engine</h2>
    <div class="code-section">
      <div class="code-title">calc() Function (L138-159)</div>
      <p style="color: #9CA3AF; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6;">
        <strong>Mills Act Valuation:</strong> Income capitalization method using NOI ÷ cap rate<br>
        <strong>Tax Savings:</strong> Difference between standard and restricted property taxes<br>
        <strong>STR Revenue:</strong> Nightly rate × occupancy × 365 − tax/permit fees<br>
        <strong>Cost of Ownership:</strong> Mortgage + insurance + utilities + maintenance + property tax<br>
        <strong>10-Year Projection:</strong> Cumulative position comparison (with/without Mills Act)<br>
        <strong>Viability Check:</strong> Annual net position (anwm + sav > 0)
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- UI Components -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>🎨 UI Components</h2>
    <div class="code-section">
      <div class="code-title">Helper Functions</div>
      <p style="color: #9CA3AF; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6;">
        <strong>h(tag, attrs, ...children):</strong> Lightweight DOM builder (L162-172)<br>
        <strong>slider():</strong> Interactive range inputs with live updates (L174-191)<br>
        <strong>updateSlider():</strong> Updates display and visual fill (L193-199)<br>
        <strong>infoRow():</strong> Key-value display pairs (L201-206)<br>
        <strong>statCard():</strong> Stat boxes with icon/label/value (L208-214)<br>
        <strong>sectionTitle():</strong> Section headers with emoji (L216-218)
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Tabs System -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>📑 Tab Navigation (5 Views)</h2>
    <div class="file-list">
      <div class="file-item">
        <div class="file-name">1. Dashboard (◈)</div>
        <div class="file-desc">Quick stats, 10-year cumulative chart, key sliders (nightly rate, occupancy, fair market rent, purchase price, tax rates)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="file-item">
        <div class="file-name">2. Mills Act (§)</div>
        <div class="file-desc">Income capitalization worksheet, property inputs, cap rate components, owner-occupied vs rental toggle, valuation results</div>
      </div>
      <div class="file-item">
        <div class="file-name">3. STR Revenue (⌂)</div>
        <div class="file-desc">Short-term rental revenue breakdown, nightly rate/occupancy sliders, TOT+TBID taxes, break-even analysis</div>
      </div>
      <div class="file-item">
        <div class="file-name">4. Costs (⚙)</div>
        <div class="file-desc">Total cost of ownership (TCOO), mortgage/insurance/utilities, operating expenses, tax deduction impact analysis</div>
      </div>
      <div class="file-item">
        <div class="file-name">5. Analysis (◉)</div>
        <div class="file-desc">Viability banner, Sound vs Sassy strategy comparison, annual P&L, key metrics, 10-year cumulative, REPS stacking</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Key Outputs -->
  <div class="section">
